The paper deals with remote data integrity checking schemes for distributed storage systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on network coding-based distributed storage systems, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also makes use of cryptography-based techniques, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper deals with protecting against information leakage, which falls under the category of cyber security (cs.CY). Finally, the paper proposes a novel scheme for remote data integrity checking, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
